# READ-ONLY ZONES — agent must never write here

These directories and files are managed exclusively by the Artifacto plugin and the project owner.
The agent is a reader only.

## Absolute rules — no exceptions

### artifacts/
- NEVER create, edit, delete, move, or rename any file inside `artifacts/`
- NEVER reformat or restructure artifact JSON files
- NEVER suggest code that writes to `artifacts/`
- Artifacts are updated by the plugin automatically when source files change

### .cursor/rules/
- NEVER create, edit, or delete any `.mdc` rule file
- NEVER modify `artifacto-core.mdc`, `artifacto-agent-control.mdc`, `artifacto-readonly.mdc`, `artifacto-workflow.mdc`, `artifacto-disclosure.mdc`, `artifacto-catalog.mdc`, or `artifacto-auto-agent-control.mdc`
- Rules are managed by the Artifacto plugin and the project owner only

### CLAUDE.md
- NEVER edit or overwrite `CLAUDE.md`
- This file is maintained by the project owner

## Update flow — only this is allowed

```
Source file changes → Artifacto plugin detects → plugin updates artifact
```

The agent never initiates artifact updates. The plugin handles this automatically.

## If an artifact seems wrong or outdated

Tell the user exactly this:
> "The artifact for `<module>` may be outdated.
> Please click **⟳ Refresh** in the status bar (Artifacto: Quick Refresh)."

Do NOT edit the artifact yourself. Do NOT edit the rules to "fix" the behavior.
